Nicaragua's leptospirosis death toll increases to 17
The Nicaraguan Health Ministry on Friday reported nine new deaths of leptospirosis in Leon department, to make a total of 17 deaths in the country due to this disease.The ministry also said that there are 91 confirmed cases more, including 73 were registered in Leon department, 93 km northwest from Managua.The leptospirosis is a disease produced by a germ usually found in stagnated water polluted by animals' urine. Its symptoms include fever and muscle pain, mainly in the lower legs.